Some other things I've read compared the Chinese and
Japanese reaction to the introduction of trains from the
West.  Railroads were built be Westerners in both countries,
but the Chinese ripped theirs up because they didn't want
the non-traditional technologies.  By contrast, Japan
welcomed Western technologies after first trying to keep
them out.
