According to the SAE Bookstore, there is an even older vehicle, the
Verbiest Steam Turbine Vehicle, a steam-turbine-powered model which
ran in the 1600s!  Per the SAE, "in the early 1670's, Ferdinand
Verbiest (1623-1688), a Flemish Jesuit missionary in China and head of
the observatory of Peking, built a small working model of steam
turbine-powered vehicle which he demonstrated at the Chinese imperial
court and which may be considered as the oldest precursor of the
automobile".  A 1995 book by Horst O. Hardenberg describes Verbiest's
model.

